# OPERATING MODE (2026-07-12, user decision): USB gadget/SSH is DISABLED;
# the serial console is the remote-access path. Rationale: enabling the
# AW9523B keyboard expander broke USB gadget enumeration (tracked in
# blockers.md B-18) — and with USB_MTU3 enabled the B-15 console mux kills
# the serial console at t=0.45s, so USB-broken + mtu3-on would leave NO
# remote access at all. Keyboard + display + serial beats USB for now.
#
# Force the SSUSB (MTU3) controller off: arm64 defconfig sets USB_MTU3=y,
# so gemini-usb.config alone being disabled is not enough. With mtu3 off
# the console mux never switches and ttyS0 (getty included) works for the
# whole session.
# CONFIG_USB_MTU3 is not set
#
# clk_ignore_unused is REQUIRED whenever USB_MTU3 is off: without mtu3
# holding its clocks, the late-boot unused-clock sweep gates something
# SSUSB-adjacent and hard-wedges the SoC (watchdog reset to Android —
# build #153, logs/2026-07-12-154). Revisit when B-18 re-enables USB.
CONFIG_CMDLINE="console=tty0 console=ttyS0,921600n1 earlycon maxcpus=8 nokaslr fbcon=rotate:3 fbcon=font:TER16x32 clk_ignore_unused"
